schema.description: Asynchronous callback request used for webhook event delivery.

data.description: The webhook event data sent to the subscribed webhook.

schema.description:
Successful response to get all delivery logs for a webhook. This returns
a paginated list of delivery logs, which can be scrolled by following the
`next` and `prev` links if present.

data.description: The list of delivery logs returned in this response.

next.description:
The link to the next page in the results. If this value is `null`
there is no next page.

prev.description:
The link to the previous page in the results. If this value is `null`
there is no previous page.

schema.description: Successful response to get a single webhook.

data.description: The webhook returned in this response.

schema.description: Successful response after creating a webhook.

Successful response to get all webhooks. This returns a paginated list of
webhooks, which can be scrolled by following the `prev` and `next` links
if present.

data.description: The list of webhooks returned in this response.

next.description:
The link to the next page in the results. If this value is `null`
there is no next page.

prev.description:
The link to the previous page in the results. If this value is `null`
there is no previous page.

schema.description: Generic error response that returns one or more errors.

errors.description: The list of errors returned in this response.

schema.description: Basic ping response to verify authentication.

id.description: The unique identifier of the authenticated customer.

statusEmoji.description: A cute emoji that represents the response status.
